adio communication techniques. Built using Laravel, PHP, MySQL, JavaScript, jQuery and Twitter Bootstrap. Development done in a Vagrant environment. Version control using Git and GitHub.</span></p><h2 class="c2"><a name="h.wj0puh61kxsr"></a><span>EventFinder</span></h2><h3 class="c8"><a name="h.8hk593fs3sag"></a><span class="c23 c18">SEPTEMBER 2015</span></h3><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Application that allows users to create and find events. Tracks event attendees, populates a calendar for each user, and displays map of event locations. Incorporates Google API, Ways Generators, and Esensi Model.</span></p><h2 class="c2"><a name="h.86dqy2rhxk4q"></a><span>Laravel Blog Project</span></h2><h3 class="c8"><a name="h.tk7m7zv6ttpw"></a><span class="c23 c18">AUGUST &nbsp;2015</span></h3><p class="c4"><span>Application for writing and viewing blog posts as well as my personal portfolio. Features user login, blog post and comment &nbsp;creation with markdown, image uploads, search functionality, and authentication to enable authors to edit posts.</span></p><h1 class="c21"><a name="h.yk8luflkpwij"></a><span>EDUCATION</span></h1><h2 class="c2"><a name="h.6wymnhinx9q5"></a><span>Codeup</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span class="c18">San Antonio, TX </span></h2><h3 class="c8"><a name="h.7vtcyzeczjot"></a><span>JUNE - OCTOBER &nbsp;2015</span></h3><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Codeup is an intensive sixteen-week boot camp for people wanting to become web programmers. I learned programming and web development with the LAMP stack: Linux/Apache/MySQL/PHP and client-side JavaScript using the Laravel framework and jQuery.</span></p><h2 class="c2"><a name="h.xwjtl6fmbrqw"></a><span>Oklahoma Christian University</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span class="c18">Edmo</span><span class="c18">nd, OK</span><span class="c18">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <p class="c4"><span class="c1"></span><span class="c11">&mdash; Mechanical Engineering</span></h2><h3 class="c8"><a name="h.miiyt1y6sl7g"></a><span>AUGUST</span><span>&nbsp;2011 - DECEMBER 2014</span></h3><p class="c4"><span>Graduated Magna Cum Laude</span><span class="c20">&nbsp;</span><span>with a bachelors of science in mechanical engineering. </span></p></td><td class="c28" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><h1 class="c21"><a name="h.ad5zax830kmu"></a><span class="c5">OBJECTIVE</span></h1><p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To use my education and programming knowledge to add value to a development team interested in creating quality applications and focused on continual growth. </span></p><h1 class="c21"><a name="h.ca0awj8022e2"></a><span class="c5">SKILLS</span></h1><ul class="c12 lst-kix_d52h1clnbs3c-0 start"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">PHP: Laravel</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Javascript: Jquery, Angular</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">mySQL</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">HTML</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">CSS</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Python</span></p><h1 class="c21"><a name="h.hrqvb4a58x88"></a><span class="c5">PERSONAL PROJECTS </span></h1><p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Arduino Uno:</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Heat and Air simulator -</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">built using circuit design, transistors, relays, motor, and heating element.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Tv Be Gone - </span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">programmed arduino with frequencies that controlled common television&rsquo;s power in order to turn them on or off using infrared LEDs.</span></p><p class="c13 c14"><span class="c5"></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class="c13"><span></span></p></body></html>
